 information about eukaryotes that lived in the blank space from roughly 800 million to 1.6 billion years ago, scientists couldn’t find the molecular fossils they expected. But when an Australian team tweaked their search filter to look for fossilized versions of more primitive molecules, they found them in abundance. The findings revealed what the authors call “a lost world” of eukaryotes that helps tell the story of the early evolutionary history of our ancient ancestors.\u003c/p>\n\u003cp>&nbsp;\u003c/p>\n","fadein":false,"__typename":"ACFContent"},"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10":{"hide_this_component":null,"acf_fc_layout":"image_component","layout":"full","regular_caption_right":true,"settings":"","attribution":"\u003cp>Tagide deCarvalho\u003c/p>\n","caption":"","mobile_comp_caption":"","mobile_comp_attribution":"","sets":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0","typename":"ImageSet"}],"__typename":"ACFImageComponent"},"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0":{"settings":"","image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0.image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0.mobile_image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_side_margins":false,"mobile_width_constraint":"","mobile_caption":"","mobile_attribution":"","zoom_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0.zoom_image","typename":"Image"},"zoom_caption":"","zoom_attribution":"","mobile_zoom_image":{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0.mobile_zoom_image","typename":"Image"},"mobile_zoom_caption":"","mobile_zoom_attribution":"","external_link":"https://www.quantamagazine.org/global-microbiome-study-gives-new-view-of-shared-health-risks-20230314/","__typename":"ImageSet"},"$Post:133073.acf.modules.10.sets.0.image":{"alt":"","caption":"","url":"https://d2r55xnwy6nx47.cloudfront.net/uploads/2023/03/TongueBiofilm-byTagide-deCarvalho-HP-scal